s called after an annotation is selected, before any callout is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"displayed for the annotation.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the return value is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"YES"},{"text":", a callout view is shown when the user taps on an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"annotation, selecting it. The default callout displays the annotation’s title","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and subtitle. You can add accessory views to either end of the callout by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implementing the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-mapView:leftCalloutAccessoryViewForAnnotation:"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"-mapView:rightCalloutAccessoryViewForAnnotation:","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" methods. You can further"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"customize the callout’s contents by implementing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"-mapView:calloutViewForAnnotation:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the return value is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NO"},{"type":"text","text":", or if this method is absent from the delegate, or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if the annotation lacks a title, the annotation will not show a callout even","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"when selected.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Related-examples","level":4,"text":"Related examples","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TODO: Add annotation views and images","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TODO: Display custom views as callouts","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"TODO: Default callout usage, learn how to show callouts for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","ident